column7: He needs to go to the nightshelter for assessment before going to a host. Can't risk putting him in a house if he has serious drug issues

(Miles Larmer) This client no longer has accommodation provided by friends. He is sleeping rough all the time. He is a recovering heroin addict so has to take drug treatments everyday. He is also having blood tests for other health problems related to pain and a loss of feeling down the left side of his body.\
He is evidently someon with significant health problems, likely to be adversly affected by constanlt sleeping rough.
